able to China’s development and security interests. In doing so, however, it is reshaping key norms of global governance towards a fundamentally illiberal direction.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aHegemony. 0aInternational relations. 0aSecurity, International. 4aGovernment & Business. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Government & Business.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981520313440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789815203134423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789815203134/original  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles